Flexbox on the parent is the modern default:

```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center; /* horizontal */
  align-items: center;     /* vertical */
}
```

If you only need horizontal centering and the div has a fixed width, `margin: 0 auto` still works fine and is simpler. For absolute positioning within a relative parent, `inset: 0; margin: auto` is clean and avoids the translate trick:

```css
.parent { position: relative; }
.child  { position: absolute; inset: 0; margin: auto; }
```

Flexbox covers most cases without fuss.
